Merge pull request #20 from psavery/fixed-rpc-sending-bug-windows-qt5.8

Fixed an rpc sending bug for Windows and Qt 5.8

Fixed an rpc sending bug for Windows and Qt 5.8

Details of the bug report submitted can be found here:

https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-61097

Basically, on Windows with the newest versions of Qt (5.8 and 5.9,
possibly earlier ones as well), two packets are sent instead of one
with the QDataStream member.

This patch circumvents that problem by creating the entire message
first and then sending it all as raw data (forcing it to be a
single packet).

This patch may be removed in the future if the Qt bug gets fixed.

Merge pull request #12 from cryos/molequeue-uit

Molequeue uit
Bring back XPath expression :-)

The call to childValues() is no longer necessary

It seems the the generated binds now do this call for us. So the
KDSoapMessage returned is just the returned value, without any
wrapping.

Fixed initialization, adjust to API changes in UIT

The job status field seems to be gone now, but we can use the job
status text field, and match on that. They changed the job ID naming
scheme to include the host name now, adjust the regular expression to
be more general.

Replaced the XPath expression with a list iteration to filter on jobs.

Basic changes for base UIT functionality

The SSL certificate is not valid, force our SSL configuration to ignore
that and connect to the server anyway. The authentication API now always
returns an error string even when authentication is proceeding as
expected so workaround that issue.
